at|mitche:  Bidding:  North can take his time with a 2@c bid.  
Since it's game-forcing, he will have a chance to discover if South has an above-minimum hand, 
in which case 6@C or 6@d (or even 6NT) might make.
I suggest a bidding sequence of 1@D - 2@c/ 2N - 4N/ pass.
Note that 4NT is quantitative, asking South to bid 6 on a maximum.
South should accept on 14 points, pass otherwise.|
