at|mitche: North might be a bit light for 4NT, since South has a maximum of 14 HCP (usually)
(with a balanced 15, South opens 1NT).
BILAsst10: I always have trouble with that unless 1 or 2 NT are opened 
- how do you quantify a good hand - min or max or just average?
mitche:  Well, I use this idea:  the fewer bids, the weaker the hand (sort of fast arrival).
So 4NT would be weaker than if North had made a third forcing bid, e.g. 3@h or 3@s over 2NT.
Note that North would not likely have a real 4-card suit for 3@h over 2NT.|
